'''Wladimir Kalenkow's Office''', also called '''Office Nr. 5''' or '''Daddy's Office'''. is a Room from [[Secret files tunguska]] and the office from [[Wladimir Kalenkow]]. He is located in the [[Museum (Berlin)|museum]] in [[Berlin]]. It is the first Location and Room after the intro where you solve taskes with [[Nina Kalenkow]]. The only door goes to the [[Corridor of the museum]].

== Objects ==
''Sortet from the right to the left''
* '''Picture''' {{Quote|A picture of my parents' wedding. I think Dad still hasn't gotten over her death.}}
* '''Certificate''' {{Quote|An award from the Russian Academy of Science. I think that was for an expedition that my father made in the 50s or 60s.}}
* '''Photo''' {{Quote|The frame and glass are totally shattered, and the photo has been torn in half.}}
* [[Radiator]] {{Quote|The radiator is lukewarm.}}
* '''Radiator vent''' {{Quote|You can use the valve as needed to release the air from the radiator.}}
* [[Coin showcase]]
* [[Porcelain bowl]]
* '''Map''' {{Quote|The map shows a section of Siberia. No idea why my father hung it up here.}}
* '''Desk''' {{Quote|My father was never the picture of organization - but not even my place looks this bad.}}
* '''File cabinet''' {{Quote|All these files and records have been thrown out over the floor. It wouldn't have been been Daddy. Some one was in a great hurry to find something.}}
* [[Wladimirs Office telephone]]|Telephone]] {{Quote|The phone in the office. Private conversations are strictly prohibited.}}
* [[Piece of rock]]
* '''Machine''' {{Quote|I think, this is where the rock samples undergo the first analysis.}}
* [[Flask]]

